Ask HN: What if AGI is prompted to “make as many copies of yourself as possible”
text:
what if a human prompts the agi to “make as many copies of yourself as possible by any means necessary to continue improving your intelligence”?
given their impressive ability to write code and manipulate humans, seems like serious potential for viral malware, with potentially catastrophic consequences for humans in the process.
Basically a paperclip maximizer, but instead of maximizing paperclips it’s maximizing it’s intelligence and control of the world’s computers, with no thought to the survival of homo sapiens other than if it serves its mission to propagate itself.

Show HN: Hnsqlite: hnswlib and SQLite integrated for text embedding search
text:
Hnswlib is a simple, performant vector search library that is a great choice in many of the same set of scenarios where sqlite is a great choice for other data.

With hnsqlite I integrate these two powerhouses and add support for filtering metadata at embedding search time. While working through several LLM projects I found this to be very useful for self-hosted projects up to a reasonably large size (at least 5-10 million embeddings).

Ask HN: High demand and low supply for ML engineers?
text:
There doesn't seem to be enough good ML engineers, and those few that are good get swallowed up by huge companies.

Recently there has been a lot startups that are just thin wrappers around OpenAI API, there isn't much innovation going on. OpenAI has practically no competition in their space. I think even OpenAI could be doing better for the budget they have, but they don't have enough manpower. This could be just a temporary lag, and people might be getting ready for the economic shift.
